Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:08.65,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.53,0:00:12.70,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Man, don't come to show off\N every time you buy a new slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:13.82,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.24,0:00:15.66,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Another young girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.99,0:00:18.20,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,You really are a lolicon, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.20,0:00:19.33,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:22.62,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Master, I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.08,0:00:25.08,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Want a bite?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.08,0:00:26.63,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.63,0:00:28.29,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Filo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.29,0:00:30.55,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, missy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.55,0:00:32.38,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,How big a bite could she take, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.01,0:00:39.10,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Time to dig in!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.06,0:00:45.31,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,That was so-so, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.21,0:01:09.34,sign_3370_33_The_Rising_of_th,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(750,645)}The Rising of the Shield Hero
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.61,0:02:24.83,sign_5367_37_Lullaby_at_Dawn,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(438,1)}A New Comrade
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.74,0:02:24.83,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's her deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:27.37,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,According to the slave merchant,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.96,0:02:32.63,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,filolials have a king or \Nqueen leading each flock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:35.13,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that just a myth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:38.92,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Those kings and queens are highly \Nskilled at transforming,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.92,0:02:42.30,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,and they blend into the flocks by \Ndisguising themselves as normal filolials.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:46.31,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,And they can transform into humans, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.31,0:02:47.77,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,That's nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.27,0:02:52.15,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, it turns out they need \Na special crest to be tamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:54.90,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't budgeted for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.24,0:03:02.53,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Things got crazy while \Ngiving her that crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.53,0:03:04.74,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Filo started resisting with all her might.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.49,0:03:10.16,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,And that was at Level 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:13.17,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows how strong she'll \Nbe at Level 70 or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:18.59,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,And? You didn't come here just to \Nshow off this filolial queen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.13,0:03:20.67,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Sell us some clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:21.63,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:23.52,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,If she rips them apart each\N time she transforms,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.52,0:03:25.60,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go broke in the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:29.52,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,There are outfits made for \Ntransforming species, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:32.65,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Those are special. I ain't got any.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:34.56,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Go see a dressmaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.56,0:03:38.61,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess you can't have her walking \Naround in public looking like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.98,0:03:40.74,main,Erh,0000,0000,0000,,Take this. Another customer left it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.32,0:03:44.28,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:47.16,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,She's cute, like an angel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:51.62,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, she has wings on her back, \Nso maybe she really is one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:55.79,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Am I cute, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:56.84,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:58.80,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't be like that, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:03:59.71,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Fath—?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.71,0:04:04.18,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Compliments help girls grow ever cuter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.39,0:04:09.26,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Master, are you my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.26,0:04:10.72,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm your owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.18,0:04:13.77,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,What about Raphtalia-oneechan, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:15.40,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,She's like my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.40,0:04:16.73,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,I am not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.73,0:04:18.32,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, that doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:19.48,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.36,0:04:25.11,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,We want clothes that don't rip when you \Ntransform and can go back to normal later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:28.45,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's what you're looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:30.95,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Did you bring magic thread?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:32.50,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Magic thread?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:37.88,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Transforming clothes are always woven using \Nthread made out of the wearer's own mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.21,0:04:41.09,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,So, they're custom made?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:41.88,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.88,0:04:44.09,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,If you give me the magic threads,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.09,0:04:48.85,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you the cutest dress ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:55.73,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Magic thread, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:59.19,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly could spin it here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.19,0:05:03.86,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,but not right now. My magic \Ngemstone broke recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.86,0:05:05.07,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is that gemstone expensive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:08.24,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,It is, but the bigger issue is \Nthat it's always in short supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.24,0:05:09.70,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:14.20,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to people and try to \Nprocure one as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:16.29,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Could you give me some time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.29,0:05:17.25,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.75,0:05:19.50,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:22.76,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,A crystal ball. It measures \None's magical affinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:24.97,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Let me check yours, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.42,0:05:27.93,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,No outfit for a while, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:32.22,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Filo has wind affinity!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.22,0:05:36.19,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,I blow away all the enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.19,0:05:40.52,top,F,0000,0000,0000,,My job is draw the carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:38.65,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.52,0:05:43.98,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,To where my Master says!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.98,0:05:47.32,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,If I find the spear guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:51.08,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send him flying with a full-power kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:54.50,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a while before we get her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:56.71,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime, let's travel \Naround and make some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:06:02.42,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,That trade pass we got from the \Nvillage lord will come in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:06.13,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Master, there's someone up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.47,0:06:09.13,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:13.10,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please, give me a ride on your carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:13.72,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:19.31,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get this medicine to the \Nvillage past the mountain at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.73,0:06:22.73,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Filo, how long will it take \Nto get there at full speed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:23.69,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Not long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:26.82,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,But we can get there even \Nsooner without the carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:29.74,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you there for one silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.16,0:06:33.87,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,But I already spent all my \Nmoney on the medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:37.58,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You can pay me in goods, \Nor even pay me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:39.25,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare try to \Nweasel out of it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.25,0:06:41.17,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.17,0:06:43.04,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the reins, Raphtalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.04,0:06:43.84,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:46.88,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:49.68,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your gratitude. \NJust make sure to pay me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:50.59,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Filo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:52.47,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Right-o!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.27,0:07:02.52,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Halt! Pay the toll!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:06.90,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back for it later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.87,0:07:16.74,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, I got you the medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:21.08,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You go boil some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:22.96,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give her the medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.96,0:07:23.92,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:25.29,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Relax. I won't charge you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:32.80,sign_12611_112_Potion_Enhance,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(107,1)}Potion Enhance
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.27,0:07:45.31,main,W,0000,0000,0000,,Why, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:46.27,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:49.53,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,The medicine's helping already?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.53,0:07:52.24,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The pain went away in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:53.91,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:08:00.91,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Um... What kind of magic spell did you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.91,0:08:03.21,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Quit asking questions you don't need to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.21,0:08:04.54,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,That aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.54,0:08:07.75,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here. This should be \Nworth one silver in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:12.30,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,That works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.30,0:08:13.47,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.47,0:08:15.68,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.55,0:08:19.52,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,On top of selling goods, I can even \Nprovide transport for people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.52,0:08:22.10,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Traveling trade may actually be \Nmore profitable than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:57.47,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I get to ride with\NOur Savior of the Heavenly Fowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:08:59.76,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,"Our Savior of the Heavenly Fowl"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.76,0:09:01.68,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,You've become quite famous \Naround these parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.18,0:09:04.23,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,"Traveling in a carriage drawn by\N the god of domesticated birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.23,0:09:08.40,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Our Savior crosses the land to treat\N the sick with his special medicine!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:10.48,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Am I a god?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:15.32,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Didn't Naofumi-sama tell you \Nnot to talk with strangers around?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.11,0:09:17.45,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.45,0:09:21.29,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,She can talk, too? That's the\Ngod of domesticated birds for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:22.70,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,She's not a god or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:26.12,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama, there are \Npeople blocking the path.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.08,0:09:31.34,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.46,0:09:34.76,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Strange bird you've got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:37.72,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,We heard an accessory seller \Nwas hitching a ride with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:40.51,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,We know you're in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:43.56,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,He was a client with baggage, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.56,0:09:48.10,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Quietly hand him over, and we'll \Nspare your lives, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.10,0:09:50.94,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you'll take \Neverything but our lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:53.82,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,You're a sharp one, lad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:58.07,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,That girl's pretty hot for a demi-human.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.07,0:10:00.87,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we can have \Nourselves some fun tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:04.50,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama, may I cut him down?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.50,0:10:06.46,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Not like you'd listen to me if I said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.33,0:10:08.37,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:10.33,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.33,0:10:13.96,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,We've got a class-upgraded bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:16.22,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.84,0:10:19.30,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Class-upgraded?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.68,0:10:21.60,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yet another unfamiliar term.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:24.93,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,If nothing else, I can tell \Nhe won't be easy pickings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:28.35,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,If only I could use support \Nmagic right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:31.73,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,As source of thy power, I order thee.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.61,0:10:36.99,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Decipher the laws of nature and \Nconceal me in a haze.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.49,0:10:38.82,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hide Mirage!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:42.37,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Fast Tornado!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.33,0:10:52.08,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Some other trader told us to \Nmug the guy riding with you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.08,0:10:54.92,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,because he was carrying \Na bunch of nice stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.92,0:10:57.26,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,One of my own sold me out, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:10:59.84,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What do we do with these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:03.72,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Usually, you'd hand them\N over to the local guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.60,0:11:07.57,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the Shield Hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.10,0:11:11.90,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,It was obvious since you had \Nno weapons, only a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:18.15,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,"We're unlucky adventurers who were \Nattacked by the cruel Shield Hero!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.15,0:11:19.32,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you'll tell the guards?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.32,0:11:21.49,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:25.08,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,They'll surely take our word \Nover the Shield Hero's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:28.50,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Then you leave me no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:30.29,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:33.50,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Filo, are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:35.04,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:36.46,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Food!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.50,0:11:39.51,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,She's an omnivore, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.51,0:11:41.05,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,And she'll gulp anything down in one go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:42.59,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you Our Savior of the Heavenly Fowl?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:44.60,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really want to commit murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:48.52,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no savior, and I need to \Nact in my best interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:51.35,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You must've killed plenty of people so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.35,0:11:54.48,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Just consider this your turn, and give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:58.40,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, please! Anything but our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:11:59.65,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:01.65,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll spare your lives, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.82,0:12:04.32,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:18.71,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're looting the bandits?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.17,0:12:21.97,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't this make us more \Nevil than the criminals?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:23.38,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.76,0:12:28.39,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,They offered up everything they had to \Npurchase their lives from Our Savior.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.39,0:12:31.85,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,He's treating even lives as merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.23,0:12:38.36,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Hero's a shining example of the \Ntrader's spirit that's so rare nowadays!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:40.94,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure this is just intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:44.99,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You two... Less talk, more work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.99,0:12:50.20,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Also, how are you going to compensate \Nme for all this trouble you caused?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:55.37,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,I offer you all the knowledge \Nand connections I possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.37,0:12:56.83,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Knowledge and connections?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.83,0:13:00.80,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I've taken a real liking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:06.05,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,The first things the accessory \Nseller taught me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:09.60,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,were how to process precious metals,\N use the tools required,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.14,0:13:13.10,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,craft gems, and imbue them with mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:21.07,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I even managed to pick up some spells, \Nthanks to getting a feel for mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:26.61,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I gained a new \Nbusiness venture: crafting gemstones.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:30.20,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Then I gained an in with \Nthe traders' grapevine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.20,0:13:32.49,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,where I heard rumors of the other heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:36.75,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Motoyasu saved a famine-stricken \Nvillage to the southwest
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.75,0:13:38.88,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,by introducing a legendary crop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:42.30,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I bet that goddamn slut put him up to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:47.72,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Ren's apparently southeast,\Nlooking for vicious monsters to slay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.72,0:13:51.10,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,I even heard a rumor that \Nsaid he took down a dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.81,0:13:56.64,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,But the information regarding Itsuki, \Nthe Bow Hero, was all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:13:58.90,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Some said he's training up in the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:01.11,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,and some said he went into a \Ndungeon on a quest for treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:06.95,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,There were even some tall tales, like him \Njoining another country's resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:09.24,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,but none of them were credible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:14.79,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,That seller certainly did provide us \Nwith ample knowledge and connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.79,0:14:18.17,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,But one thing he offered helped \Nme more than any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.96,0:14:25.84,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this deed is genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:29.84,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed that grumpy money-grubber \Nactually gave this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.26,0:14:34.01,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if there's a gemstone you want,\N I can arrange getting it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:37.43,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,At a discount, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.43,0:14:39.19,main,G,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.56,0:14:42.11,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I want the gemstone used \Nto make magic threads.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.61,0:14:51.78,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed you learned where to \Nfind that gemstone so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.78,0:14:53.66,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's not all good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.16,0:14:56.79,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to be in a rather dicey location.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:14:58.08,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:10.55,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,This temple was once a notoriously\N evil alchemist's base of operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:14.43,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,I never knew there was a tunnel here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.85,0:15:17.10,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,According to the mining chief,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:20.23,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,nobody's dared approach this place \Nsince some monsters nested here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.69,0:15:21.90,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Stay on your toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:33.49,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.20,0:15:35.37,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,That's ancient writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:39.33,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,"We pray this seed never \Nmakes it out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:43.00,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,It is a horribly twisted \Nmanifestation of our wish
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.00,0:15:45.88,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,for nobody to starve."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:50.09,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like some bandits already \Nreleased it into the world, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:53.59,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Master, there's a path down this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:55.14,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:01.56,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Filo! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.56,0:16:02.56,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:04.36,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:05.44,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.19,0:16:07.32,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:12.03,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,If you won't listen to me, \Nthen I don't need you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:17.45,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.04,0:16:18.74,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.50,0:16:21.41,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,A monster footprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:23.75,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,It must be a rather large one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:28.00,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,But we have to keep going until \Nwe get what we're here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.00,0:16:28.88,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Just be care—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:31.80,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.80,0:16:33.01,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Stay calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:34.55,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, witch! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.93,0:16:38.81,italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick and tired of being \NNaofumi-sama's slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:43.10,italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I only pretended to become his slave again\N so I could kill him with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:46.40,italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I can stab him clean \Nthrough from behind now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.40,0:16:48.15,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let the voices mislead you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:48.90,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,The witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:52.53,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,The monsters here provoke you by saying \Nthe last things you want to hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:54.78,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,in the last voices you want saying them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:56.74,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,How nasty is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.74,0:16:58.95,italics,F,0000,0000,0000,,Master is my food!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.08,0:17:01.83,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, something cut me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:03.00,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Do something about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.41,0:17:05.75,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,As source of thy power, I order thee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.13,0:17:10.42,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Decipher the laws of nature and \Nrestore our sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.42,0:17:12.26,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Fast Anti-Bind!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.97,0:17:16.55,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,If we can see them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.55,0:17:17.05,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Filo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:20.14,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna blow you away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.93,0:17:25.98,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.98,0:17:27.15,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.61,0:17:34.86,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think this will come in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.07,0:17:34.86,sign_28483_277_Voice_Gengar_Shi,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(237,1)}Voice Gengar Shield (Bat Form)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.99,0:17:37.24,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Let's keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:41.49,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,You won't abandon me, right, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:43.33,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I've got money riding on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.33,0:17:45.12,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I won't get rid of you easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:46.87,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.25,0:17:48.75,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.21,0:17:54.21,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama would never say mean things \Nlike those hallucinations you heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.55,0:17:56.97,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll believe in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.43,0:18:03.39,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.56,0:18:07.69,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Something's in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:17.95,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,That's the gemstone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:19.87,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.37,0:18:25.12,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,That's a nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.12,0:18:27.46,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,It's on the small side, but still dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:29.08,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.08,0:18:32.13,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,The gemstone's right there, \Nbut we can't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.13,0:18:32.96,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're going!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.05,0:18:36.26,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Those two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.26,0:18:37.80,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Cover us, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:46.93,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Zweit Fire Blast!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:52.36,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Naofumi-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:56.69,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Can I hold it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:18:58.74,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:01.07,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:07.20,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,That was close...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:10.12,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,We need to avoid that at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:13.04,italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,But then how do we attack it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.17,0:19:18.97,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out, Raphtalia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.84,0:19:21.93,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,It can see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:23.97,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,No. It hears her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.97,0:19:26.93,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,It's really sensitive to sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:28.23,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.10,0:19:35.40,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Filo! Yell in here as loud as you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:35.98,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.98,0:19:38.11,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, cover your ears!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:42.95,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.95,0:19:45.16,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Zweit Fire Blast!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.21,0:19:58.76,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,We won!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.21,0:20:00.34,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are you unhurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.34,0:20:01.09,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:02.55,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:03.93,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.93,0:20:07.01,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Don't charge in so recklessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.01,0:20:07.89,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.27,0:20:11.94,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,What if you got a scar that never faded?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.94,0:20:14.02,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,You're worried about my...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.02,0:20:15.31,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are we clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:16.52,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:18.90,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:25.95,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,It really is beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:39.63,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,This is making me tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:42.97,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you're converting \Nyour mana into thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:44.97,main,OldMag,0000,0000,0000,,Endure it for just a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:48.93,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a snack once you finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.93,0:20:51.56,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,A yummy one? Then I'll keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.16,0:21:10.16,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,How do I look, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.16,0:21:11.83,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.83,0:21:15.00,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! Thank you, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.37,0:21:17.96,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, sure, she looks cute...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.96,0:21:19.09,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.09,0:21:25.58,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,I did my very best to bring out every \Nlast bit of Filo-chan's angelic charm!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.58,0:21:28.36,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,I used white as the base color,\N to go with her wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.36,0:21:31.59,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,I added in plenty of frills as \Na nod to her feathers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.59,0:21:35.00,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,And since it'd contrast \Nbest with her blonde hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.00,0:21:37.00,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,I went with blue for the ribbon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.00,0:21:38.51,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:44.14,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,The monster crest and magic outfit \Nadd up to 340 silvers in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.14,0:21:46.41,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better work hard to pay it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.41,0:21:48.88,main,F,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:53.05,main,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't suddenly transform indoors!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:58.14,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,The ribbon looks oh-so-cute \Neven in her monster form!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.14,0:22:00.08,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:02.51,main,Dre,0000,0000,0000,,You agree, don't you, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.51,0:22:03.77,main,N,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me!
